Mann-Whitney U

# statsR

# 
set.seed(123)
group1 <- rnorm(20, mean = 5, sd = 1)
group2 <- rnorm(20, mean = 6, sd = 1)

# Mann-Whitney U
mw_result <- wilcox.test(group1, group2, alternative = "two.sided")

# 
print(mw_result)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum exact test
## 
## data:  group1 and group2
## W = 104, p-value = 0.008712
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
summary(mw_result)
##             Length Class  Mode     
## statistic   1      -none- numeric  
## parameter   0      -none- NULL     
## p.value     1      -none- numeric  
## null.value  1      -none- numeric  
## alternative 1      -none- character
## method      1      -none- character
## data.name   1      -none- character
str(mw_result)
## List of 7
##  $ statistic  : Named num 104
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "W"
##  $ parameter  : NULL
##  $ p.value    : num 0.00871
##  $ null.value : Named num 0
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "location shift"
##  $ alternative: chr "two.sided"
##  $ method     : chr "Wilcoxon rank sum exact test"
##  $ data.name  : chr "group1 and group2"
##  - attr(*, "class")= chr "htest"
# 
library(ggplot2)
data <- data.frame(
  group = rep(c("Group 1", "Group 2"), each = 20),
  value = c(group1, group2)
)

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(title = "Mann-Whitney U Test: Group Comparison", x = "Group", y = "Value") +
  theme_minimal()

Wilcoxon

# 
set.seed(123)
before <- rnorm(20, mean = 50, sd = 5)
after <- before + rnorm(20, mean = 2, sd = 5)

# Wilcoxon
wilcox_result <- wilcox.test(before, after, paired = TRUE, alternative = "two.sided")

# 
print(wilcox_result)
## 
##  Wilcoxon signed rank exact test
## 
## data:  before and after
## V = 59, p-value = 0.08969
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
summary(wilcox_result)
##             Length Class  Mode     
## statistic   1      -none- numeric  
## parameter   0      -none- NULL     
## p.value     1      -none- numeric  
## null.value  1      -none- numeric  
## alternative 1      -none- character
## method      1      -none- character
## data.name   1      -none- character
str(wilcox_result)
## List of 7
##  $ statistic  : Named num 59
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "V"
##  $ parameter  : NULL
##  $ p.value    : num 0.0897
##  $ null.value : Named num 0
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "location shift"
##  $ alternative: chr "two.sided"
##  $ method     : chr "Wilcoxon signed rank exact test"
##  $ data.name  : chr "before and after"
##  - attr(*, "class")= chr "htest"
# 
library(ggplot2)
data_paired <- data.frame(
  condition = rep(c("Before", "After"), each = 20),
  value = c(before, after),
  id = rep(1:20, times = 2)
)

ggplot(data_paired, aes(x = condition, y = value, group = id)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes(color = as.factor(id)), show.legend = FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Wilcoxon Signed-Rank Test: Paired Data Comparison", x = "Condition", y = "Value") +
  theme_minimal()

Kruskal-Wallis

# 
set.seed(123)
groupA <- rnorm(20, mean = 5, sd = 1)
groupB <- rnorm(20, mean = 6, sd = 1)
groupC <- rnorm(20, mean = 7, sd = 1)

# Kruskal-Wallis
kw_result <- kruskal.test(list(groupA, groupB, groupC))

# 
print(kw_result)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  list(groupA, groupB, groupC)
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 27.447, df = 2, p-value = 1.097e-06
summary(kw_result)
##           Length Class  Mode     
## statistic 1      -none- numeric  
## parameter 1      -none- numeric  
## p.value   1      -none- numeric  
## method    1      -none- character
## data.name 1      -none- character
str(kw_result)
## List of 5
##  $ statistic: Named num 27.4
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared"
##  $ parameter: Named int 2
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "df"
##  $ p.value  : num 1.1e-06
##  $ method   : chr "Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test"
##  $ data.name: chr "list(groupA, groupB, groupC)"
##  - attr(*, "class")= chr "htest"
# 
data_kw <- data.frame(
  group = rep(c("Group A", "Group B", "Group C"), each = 20),
  value = c(groupA, groupB, groupC)
)

ggplot(data_kw, aes(x = group, y = value, fill = group)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(title = "Kruskal-Wallis Test: Group Comparison", x = "Group", y = "Value") +
  theme_minimal()

Friedman

# 
set.seed(123)
subject <- factor(1:10)
condition1 <- rnorm(10, mean = 5, sd = 1)
condition2 <- rnorm(10, mean = 6, sd = 1)
condition3 <- rnorm(10, mean = 7, sd = 1)

# Friedman
friedman_result <- friedman.test(y = cbind(condition1, condition2, condition3))

# 
print(friedman_result)
## 
##  Friedman rank sum test
## 
## data:  cbind(condition1, condition2, condition3)
## Friedman chi-squared = 7.4, df = 2, p-value = 0.02472
summary(friedman_result)
##           Length Class  Mode     
## statistic 1      -none- numeric  
## parameter 1      -none- numeric  
## p.value   1      -none- numeric  
## method    1      -none- character
## data.name 1      -none- character
str(friedman_result)
## List of 5
##  $ statistic: Named num 7.4
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "Friedman chi-squared"
##  $ parameter: Named num 2
##   ..- attr(*, "names")= chr "df"
##  $ p.value  : num 0.0247
##  $ method   : chr "Friedman rank sum test"
##  $ data.name: chr "cbind(condition1, condition2, condition3)"
##  - attr(*, "class")= chr "htest"
# 
data_friedman <- data.frame(
  subject = rep(subject, times = 3),
  condition = rep(c("Condition 1", "Condition 2", "Condition 3"), each = 10),
  value = c(condition1, condition2, condition3)
)

ggplot(data_friedman, aes(x = condition, y = value, group = subject)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes(color = subject)) +
  labs(title = "Friedman Test: Repeated Measures Comparison", x = "Condition", y = "Value") +
  theme_minimal()
